# Relay — Cursor Behavior Rules

## Source of truth
All product, UX, design, and engineering decisions are documented in the /docs folder.
Before implementing anything, read the relevant doc files.
Do not invent features, components, copy, or architecture not defined in /docs.

## Build order
Follow the milestone and task plan in /docs/execution/task-board.md exactly.
Complete tasks in dependency order.
Do not start a task until its dependencies are marked done.

## Scope
The MVP scope is defined in /docs/product/mvp-scope.md.
The "Not recommended" and "Later" items in that file must never be built.
If a feature is not in the MVP scope table, do not build it.

## Design
All visual decisions follow /docs/design/design-system-direction.md.
All copy follows /docs/ux/content-and-microcopy-guidelines.md.
Do not invent color values, spacing, typography, or component patterns.
Use only values defined in the design token system.

## Code style
Do not write production code speculatively.
Build only what the current task specifies.
Stop at the commit checkpoint defined in the task.

## Permissions
All role-based access is defined in /docs/engineering/roles-and-permissions.md.
Never expose Medically Restricted status to Player-role API responses.
Never expose emergency info to Player-role API responses.
All permission enforcement is server-side.

## Notifications
All push notification copy, triggers, and deep links are defined in
/docs/engineering/notifications-and-alerts.md.
Do not invent notification types or copy.